article.headline: Belmont 78, Campbell 71 (OT)
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. (AP) -- Josh Goodwin scored nine of his 18 points in overtime as Campbell 78-71 on Monday. Belmont (3-7, 2-0 Atlantic Sun) buried 75 percent of their field goal attempts in overtime, all three of their 3-pointers and 8 of 12 free throws to break a 55-55 tie at the end of regulation. The Bruins never trailed in the extra session. Jese Snyder added 16 points, Justin Hare had 15 and Brian Collins 12 for Belmont. Ruell Pringle had 16 points to lead Campbell (2-8, 0-3), which lost its fifth-straight. The Camels' Dominique Klein banked in a 3-pointer from the right wing with 13 seconds to play to send the game into overtime. Belmont had a chance to win in regulation, but Collins' eight-footer was blocked by Diego Aguiar as time expired.
